Then, they brought the garlic bread.
It was that soggy over-buttered, undercooked, nastiness you would never get in Italy or even a high-end Italian restaurant in the states.
(Think Fazoli's)  The greasiness probably started to take away my appetite which had been sky high when I arrived.
I would strongly recommend that Ruffino's ditch the garlic bread and go with nice Italian bread and small bowl of butter.
Soon after, the entrees for the neighboring table arrived.
They didn't look like $25-30 entrees.
Even the osso bucco looked unappetizing..  Then, they brought me a cup of brodo with tortellini.
